{"lemma":"أَغْرِبَة","slug":"أَغْرِبَة","root":"غ.ر.ب","root_slug":"غ-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"غُراب","root":"غرب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31615"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%BA%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"crow, raven","examples":[{"text":"فَبَعَثَ ٱللَّهُ غُرَابٗا يَبۡحَثُ فِي ٱلۡأَرۡض لِيُرِيَهُۥ كَيۡفَ يُوَٰرِي سَوۡءَةَ أَخِيهِۚ قَالَ يَٰوَيۡلَتَىٰٓ أَعَجَزۡتُ أَنۡ أَكُونَ مِثۡلَ هَٰذَا ٱلۡغُرَابِ فَأُوَٰرِيَ سَوۡءَةَ أَخِيۖ فَأَصۡبَحَ مِنَ ٱلنَّٰدِمِينَ.","english":"Then Allah sent a raven scratching up the ground, to show him how to hide his brother's naked corpse. He said: \"Woe unto me! Am I not able to be as this raven and so hide my brother's naked corpse? And he became repentant."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a ship, corvet, sloop"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bend of the scabbard"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"edge, point"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ḡurayb- (“crow, raven”). Compare Hebrew עוֹרֵב / עֹרֵב ('orév), Aramaic עורבא (ʿurbaʾ)."},"ipa":["/ɣu.raːb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31615","headword_ar":"غُرَابٌ","root":"grb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain black bird,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corvus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which there are several species;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[namely, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raven, carrioncrow, rook, jackdaw, jay, magpie,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.:] and it was used as a proper name, which, as is said in a trad., he [i. e. Mohammad] changed, because the word implies the meaning of distance, and because it is the name of a foul bird: (TA:) the pl. [of mult.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"girobaAnN","text_ar":"غِرْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurobN","text_ar":"غُرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and (of pauc., S)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agoribapN","text_ar":"اَغْرِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agorubN","text_ar":"اَغْرُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K;) and pl. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garaAbiynu","text_ar":"غَرَابِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) When the Arabs characterize a land as fertile, they say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaEa fiY A^aroDK laA yuTay~aru guraAbuhaA","text_ar":"وَقَعَ فِى اَرْضٍ لَا يُطَيَّرُ غُرَابُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lighted upon a land of which the crow will not be made to fly away;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of its abundant herbage: see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tay~ara","text_ar":"طَيَّرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajada vamarapa AlguraAbi","text_ar":"وَجَدَ ثَمَرَةَ الغُرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He found the fruit of the crow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because that bird seeks after and chooses the most excellent of fruits. (TA.) They also say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAra guraAbu fulaAnK","text_ar":"طَارَ غُرَابُ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The crow of such a one flew away"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the head of such a one became white,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hoary."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA. [See also a similar phrase below.]) Also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN A^aboSaru mino","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ اَبْصَرُ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guraAbK","text_ar":"غُرَابٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is more sharp-sighted than a crow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHo*aru","text_ar":"اَحْذَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more cautious"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azohaY","text_ar":"اَزْهَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more proud"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oA^amu","text_ar":"اَشْاَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more inauspicious"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: &c.: they say that this bird is more inauspicious than any other inauspicious thing upon the earth. (TA.) In the phrase ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guraAbN gaAribN","text_ar":"غُرَابٌ غَارِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the epithet is added to give intensiveness to the signification. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guraAbu Albayoni","text_ar":"غُرَابُ البَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has been expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byn","text_ar":"بين"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlguraAbu","text_ar":"الغُرَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One of the southern constellations,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Corvus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting of seven stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the enumeration of Ptolemy"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behind"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaATiyap","text_ar":"البَاطِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Crater"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the south of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~imaAku AlA^aEozalu","text_ar":"السِّمَاكُ الاَعْزَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Spica Virginis"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Kzw.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agoribapu AlEarabi","text_ar":"اَغْرِبَةُ العَرَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The blacks"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crows"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Arabs; the black Arabs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) likened to the birds called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Agrbp","text_ar":"اغربة"},{"kind":"text","text":", in respect of their complexion: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in all of them the blackness was derived from their mothers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF, TA.) The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agoribap","text_ar":"اَغْرِبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Time of Ignorance were 'Antarah and Khufáf Ibn-Nudbeh (asserted to have been a Mukhadram, TA) and Aboo-'Omeyr Ibn-El- Hobáb and Suleyk Ibn-Es-Sulakeh (a famous runner, TA) and Hishám Ibn-'Okbeh-Ibn-AbeeMo'eyt; but this last was a Mukhadram: and those among the Islámees, 'Abd-Allah Ibn-Khá- zim and 'Omeyr Ibn-Abee-'Omeyr and Hemmám [in the CK Humám] Ibn-Mutarrif and Munteshir Ibn-Wahb and Matar Ibn-Abee-Owfà and Taäbbata-Sharrà and Esh-Shenfarà and Hájiz; to the last of whom is given no appellation of the kind called “ nisbeh, ” (K, TA,) in relation to father, mother, tribe, or place. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijolu AlguraAbi","text_ar":"رِجْلُ الغُرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain herb, called in the language of the Barbar"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iToriylaAl","text_ar":"اـِطْرِيلَال"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in the present day"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zir~u AlA^axil~api","text_ar":"زِرُّ الاَخِلَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MF,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ibiv~","text_ar":"شِبِثّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v., variously written in different copies of the K,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in its stem and in its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jum~ap","text_ar":"جُمَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"node whence the flower grows"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in its lower part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"root, except that its flower is white, and it forms grains like those of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqoduwnis","text_ar":"مَقْدُونِس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scandix cerefolium"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apium petroselinum"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) a drachm of its seeds, bruised, and mixed with honey (K, TA) deprived of its froth, (TA,) is a tried medicine for eradicating [the species of leprosy which are called] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraS","text_ar":"بَرَص"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bahaq","text_ar":"بَهَق"},{"kind":"text","text":", being drunk; and sometimes is added to it a quarter of a drachm of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAqiro qaroHaA","text_ar":"عَاقِرْ قَرْحَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) which is [commonly] known by the name of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ewd AlqrH","text_ar":"عود القرح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euwdu AlqaroHi","text_ar":"عُودُ القَرْحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", both of these being names now applied to pyrethrum, i. e. pellitory of Spain, but the latter, accord. to Forskål (Flora Ægypt. Arab. p. cxix.), applied in El-Yemen to the cacalia sonchifolia, or to a species of senecio]; (TA;) the patient sitting in a hot sun, with the diseased parts uncovered: (K, TA:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijolN","text_ar":"رِجْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": now applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chelidonium hybridum"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linn.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chelidonium dodecandrum"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Forsk.: (Delile's Floræ Ægypt. Illustr. no. 502:) in Bocthor's Dict. Français-Arabe, both the names of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rjl","text_ar":"رجل"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgrAb","text_ar":"الغراب"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ATrylAl","text_ar":"اطريلال"},{"kind":"text","text":"are given to the plants called"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cerfeuil"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chervil"},{"kind":"text","text":") and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corne de cerf"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"buck'shorn plantain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coronopus"},{"kind":"text","text":").] ―         -b5-  Also (i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijolu AlguraAbi","text_ar":"رِجْلُ الغُرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain mode of binding the udder of a camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tightly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that the young one cannot suck;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor will it undo."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Hence] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sur~a Ealayohi rijolu AlguraAbi","text_ar":"صُرَّ عَلَيْهِ رِجْلُ الغُرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The affair was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, difficult,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strait, to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his life,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subsistence, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, so."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [And in like manner one says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSar~a","text_ar":"اَصَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to the TA: but this I think doubtful; believing that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSar~a","text_ar":"اَصَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sar~a","text_ar":"صَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning that one says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sar~a","text_ar":"صَرَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi rijola AlguraAbi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ رِجْلَ الغُرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bound him with a bond not to be undone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that would not undo;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he straitened him."},{"kind":"text","text":"See, again,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijolN","text_ar":"رِجْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and a verse there cited as an ex.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlguraAbaAni","text_ar":"الغُرَابَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two lower extremities of the two hips,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"haunches, that are next to the upper parts of the thighs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the heads,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"highest parts, of the hips,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"haunches:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two thin bones, lower than what is called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraA$ap","text_ar":"فَرَاشَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or, app.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraA$","text_ar":"فَرَاش"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]: (K, TA:) or, in a horse and in a camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two extremities of the haunches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their two edges, on the left and right, that are above the tail, at the junction of the head of the haunch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where the upper parts of the haunch, on the right and left, meet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two extremities of the haunch that are behind the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaAp","text_ar":"قَطَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fore part of the croup"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (IAar, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"girobaAnN","text_ar":"غِرْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": Dhu-r-Rummeh says, referring to camels,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"taqaw~aba Eano girobaAni A^aworaAkihaA AlxaToru"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqaw~abato girobaAnuhaA Eani AlxaTori","text_ar":"تَقَوَّبَتْ غِرْبَانُهَا عَنِ الخَطْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The prominences of their haunches were excoriated from the lashing with the tails"},{"kind":"text","text":"], the phrase being inverted, for the meaning is known; (S in this art.;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqaw~aba","text_ar":"تَقَوَّبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaw~aba","text_ar":"قَوَّبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the saying means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the lashing with the tails excoriated the prominences of the haunches"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xTr","text_ar":"خطر"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"girobaAnN","text_ar":"غِرْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"haunches"},{"kind":"text","text":"themselves, of camels: and is employed [by a synecdoche] to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"[themselves]: (IAar, TA:) and [the sing.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guraAbN","text_ar":"غُرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also expl. as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity of the haunch that is next the back."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guraAbN","text_ar":"غُرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whole of the back of the head."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAba guraAbuhu","text_ar":"شَابَ غُرَابُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hair of the whole of the back of his head became white,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hoary."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See a similar phrase above in this paragraph.]) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurobN","text_ar":"غُرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", former half, in two places.       -A3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bunch"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariyr","text_ar":"بَرِير"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or fruit of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araAk","text_ar":"اَرَاك"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a black bunch"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"girobaAnN","text_ar":"غِرْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"girobaAnu","text_ar":"غِرْبَانُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albariyri","text_ar":"البَرِيرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the ripe fruit of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araAk","text_ar":"اَرَاك"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)       -A4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hail,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"snow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hoar-frost:"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mugorabN","text_ar":"مُغْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying the “ dawn; ” because of their whiteness. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","Msb","K","MF","As","IAar"]}]}}